ull, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7769": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_56b13_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1391187 - Compare build id to perform full directory scan in addon manager. r=kmag, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4ex9JrMm3NT", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/internal/XPIProvider.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5b3d123eee2431d79cf1065d7564b820992a2a31", "parents": ["a01f8c3ec5e90e360f1fd02043cb7282ad739e31"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kelly \u003cmkelly@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_56b13_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1399245 - Fix mozilla/normandy#1036: Remove OSX-specific close button CSS for Heartbeat bar. r=Gijs, a=lizzard\n\nDue to changes in browser styles for Photon, the fix is no longer necessary, and\nin fact makes the close button look wrong. Without the fix, the close button\nlooks and behaves the same as the tab bar close buttons.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 89tCvQAq1OR", "files": ["browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/skin/osx/Heartbeat.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b6d27f6b9830700c29009f55f1f1a5d39b470d7b", "parents": ["5b3d123eee2431d79cf1065d7564b820992a2a31"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kelly \u003cmkelly@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_56b13_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1399245 - Fix mozilla/normandy#1058: Bind PreferenceExperiment driver functions. r=Gijs, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7e6f6QdHdVf", "files": ["browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/lib/NormandyDriver.jsm", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/test/browser/browser_NormandyDriver.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7ff6b593e6623f6ec9e42344ffe944ba32965395", "parents": ["b6d27f6b9830700c29009f55f1f1a5d39b470d7b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Parks \u003cdparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_56b13_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1394024 - Handle null string when alerting plugin about Windows microphone change. r=jimm, a=lizzard\n\nFixes crash when unplugging the only available microphone.", "files": ["dom/plugins/ipc/PluginUtilsWin.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "55870ef25cdebebd460c446a66ba245847afe29b", "parents": ["7ff6b593e6623f6ec9e42344ffe944ba32965395"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Munro Mengjue Chiang \u003cmchiang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_56b13_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1399395 - Skip devicechange event handler in shutdown stage. r=pehrsons, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8skWP7LuGvR", "files": ["dom/media/MediaManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0bfaf562bf40e775ab7f91c8ad8e7c0f7a8bfa14", "parents": ["55870ef25cdebebd460c446a66ba245847afe29b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_56b13_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1396307 - Make sure we only set mRaceCacheWithNetwork to true when the feature is enabled. r=michal, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FrLjfuExmYV", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpChannel.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a3e692e095c61825b6c6727da13e1097b6a250d8", "parents": ["0bfaf562bf40e775ab7f91c8ad8e7c0f7a8bfa14"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Conley \u003cmconley@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_56b13_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1399796 - UnsubmittedCrashHandler should never check for unsubmitted crash reports if disabled or suppressed. r=Felipe, a=lizzard on a CLOSED TREE\n\nBug 1355492 moved the logic for scanning for unsubmitted crash reports out of the initialization\nof UnsubmittedCrashHandler, and the initialization is what decided whether or not it was\nappropriate to scan in the first place. This was done so that scanning could be deferred\nuntil idle after first paint.\n\nThis patch makes it so that the scanning logic first ensures that the UnsubmittedCrashHandler\nis actually enabled and not suppressed (which is calculated earlier).\n\nI've also taken the liberty of adding a regression test.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3Aihom5Q17R", "files": ["browser/modules/ContentCrashHandlers.jsm", "browser/modules/test/browser/browser_UnsubmittedCrashHandler.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a841920fd8cbaa5f026f699cc64300a00681b8f7", "parents": ["a3e692e095c61825b6c6727da13e1097b6a250d8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505593110, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7770": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_56b13_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Backed out changeset fce8bb3c16f7 (bug 1389021) for breaking debug builds on a CLOSED TREE.", "files": ["gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorManagerParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorManagerParent.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorThread.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "27102a84d91e04644a85d9799e006ea726f0fb2b", "parents": ["a841920fd8cbaa5f026f699cc64300a00681b8f7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505610784, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7771": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395879 - Remove espree/escope etc from the direct dependencies of eslint-plugin-mozilla since they are really peerDependencies supplied by the existing eslint peer. r=mossop\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2FEfFaEoomU", "files": ["npm-shrinkwrap.json", "tools/lint/eslint/eslint-plugin-mozilla/manifest.tt", "tools/lint/eslint/eslint-plugin-mozilla/package-lock.json", "tools/lint/eslint/eslint-plugin-mozilla/package.json", "tools/lint/eslint/manifest.tt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "740cc074c30ff143f3716c59e591bd1ac2f392d9", "parents": ["f90546e2947f1cc8381b4faf2c61e6cedc85831e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bobby Holley \u003cbobbyholley@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #18532 - Undo #18497 in the MatchAndCascade case (from bholley:more_cache_insertion); r=emilio\n\nIt's easy to construct examples where not inserting in those cases causes performance\nto get worse (for example, any long list of siblings that match the same selectors\nwhile having some non-effectual differences in LocalName/Class/Id/etc). And the LRU\nnature of the cache already does the right thing of pruning non-useful entries.\n\nFixing this causes several hundred more sharing hits on wikipedia.\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: da64abc4298549362debc96e5843bd36e6d23b7f", "files": ["servo/components/style/sharing/mod.rs", "servo/components/style/traversal.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b1e13cff22b9fa9ed414cf60f44b850e95603e1f", "parents": ["740cc074c30ff143f3716c59e591bd1ac2f392d9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "merge mozilla-central to autoland. r=merge a=merge", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-fonts-3/font-kerning-03.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "5e5e2372b2c05bf68b4cd0908bdf22d8c4575a9d", "parents": ["b1e13cff22b9fa9ed414cf60f44b850e95603e1f", "27e7b4261e4b5a016e09adb5332a181e43ab520e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Manish Goregaokar \u003cmanishsmail@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #18492 - stylo: Preserve variants of 2d translate/rotate/scale functions in computed transform (from Manishearth:stylo-translate); r=hiikezoe\n\nNecessary for the animation inspector to show the right thing.\n\nr=hiikezoe https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1391145\n\nfixes bug 1391145\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 90689b791669c7b9d13695b2ad88b08ec5d99e05", "files": ["servo/components/style/properties/gecko.mako.rs", "servo/components/style/properties/helpers/animated_properties.mako.rs", "servo/components/style/properties/longhand/box.mako.rs", "servo/components/style/values/computed/transform.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "616bd23b9896a311973adadd932a76459cc634e4", "parents": ["5e5e2372b2c05bf68b4cd0908bdf22d8c4575a9d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brad Werth \u003cbwerth@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #18526 - Prevent aspect-ratio media queries from causing m\u2026 (from bradwerth:aspectOverflow); r=emilio\n\n\u2026ultiplication overflow by extending values to u64.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: e4kfxMDvZh\n\n\u003c!-- Please describe your changes on the following line: --\u003e\nhttps://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1399941\nhttps://reviewboard.mozilla.org/r/179984/\n\n---\n\u003c!-- Thank you for contributing to Servo! Please replace each `[ ]` by `[X]` when the step is complete, and replace `__` with appropriate data: --\u003e\n- [X] `./mach build -d` does not report any errors\n- [X] `./mach test-tidy` does not report any errors\n- [ ] These changes fix #__ (github issue number if applicable).\n\n\u003c!-- Either: --\u003e\n- [ ] There are tests for these changes OR\n- [X] These changes do not require tests because tests are in Gecko code.\n\n\u003c!-- Also, please make sure that \"Allow edits from maintainers\" checkbox is checked, so that we can help you if you get stuck somewhere along the way.--\u003e\n\n\u003c!-- Pull requests that do not address these steps are welcome, but they will require additional verification as part of the review process. --\u003e\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 4c04ece8c57cdd14bdaba21beae2d2e390dd1527", "files": ["servo/components/style/gecko/media_queries.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "375708697623fe63e87bf2e28ecd29a250c3a7ee", "parents": ["616bd23b9896a311973adadd932a76459cc634e4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nihanth Subramanya \u003cnhnt11@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1370401 - Don't allow URL bar width to shrink smaller than its contents. r=dao,Gijs\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: yUldCs59cZ", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.css", "browser/base/content/browser.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5dc35eb2c70b5e60e334e9b8a779dc5dd273608a", "parents": ["375708697623fe63e87bf2e28ecd29a250c3a7ee"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1399499 - Add additional margin-top to the tabs toolbar on Windows 7 per Photon spec. r=nhnt11\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: E3lWYq29eTQ", "files": ["browser/themes/windows/browser.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "134474e7c8a93b2565502b4a751a8ed0a0819512", "parents": ["5dc35eb2c70b5e60e334e9b8a779dc5dd273608a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 616bd23b9896 (bug 1391145) for frequently failing mochitests layout/style/test/test_animations.html and layout/style/test/test_animations_omta.html on Linux x64. r=backout", "files": ["servo/components/style/properties/gecko.mako.rs", "servo/components/style/properties/helpers/animated_properties.mako.rs", "servo/components/style/properties/longhand/box.mako.rs", "servo/components/style/values/computed/transform.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "092944affb617ed74cd494a8feb7ac99fba2100a", "parents": ["134474e7c8a93b2565502b4a751a8ed0a0819512"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 5dc35eb2c70b (bug 1370401) on request from nhnt11 (taking bug 1399235 into account). r=backout", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.css", "browser/base/content/browser.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "733123f73cedfc198788848594bdc83adc3f9188", "parents": ["092944affb617ed74cd494a8feb7ac99fba2100a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozi