s or http version of the page. r=ursula\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3W3OUu0gffH", "files": ["toolkit/modules/NewTabUtils.jsm", "toolkit/modules/tests/xpcshell/test_NewTabUtils.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "26f9c5c3f434500adb3aa7e47c8eebdb9ed45c86", "parents": ["f39fd02e1dc8cf5098b4bf962ed492ef01e3e06f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1400243 - 1. Use universal DoorHanger in LoginManagerPrompter; r=esawin\n\nUse the universal DoorHanger API from Prompt.jsm to show the login\ndoorhanger from any window. Also, refactor parts of LoginManagerPrompter\nto use Services.jsm if possible.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3cnzeT0RNgR", "files": ["mobile/android/components/LoginManagerPrompter.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ef0402ba21c23c957c6ffb56671c10a2680f4005", "parents": ["26f9c5c3f434500adb3aa7e47c8eebdb9ed45c86"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1400243 - 2. Small fixes to ActionBarHandler and FormAssistant; r=esawin\n\nSmall fixes to ride-along in this bug:\n* Use localized ellipsis in ActionBarHandler if available.\n* Fix one situation where the FormAssistPopup fails to hide.\n* Handle an error case in FormAssistant.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9EZhPnS5h3E", "files": ["mobile/android/modules/ActionBarHandler.jsm", "mobile/android/modules/FormAssistant.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f07a6fbba625da26526a24fe04bd01b1f40b1a1b", "parents": ["ef0402ba21c23c957c6ffb56671c10a2680f4005"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brian Grinstead \u003cbgrinstead@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397295 - Use environment variables instead of query string for params to Browser Toolbox;r=jryans\n\nThis allows data like screen position to be persisted in the xul store for the document\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4vdbkneckXh", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/ToolboxProcess.jsm", "devtools/client/framework/toolbox-process-window.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ad4a5b8426edef77c9e2ed9aba138083c9937e64", "parents": ["f07a6fbba625da26526a24fe04bd01b1f40b1a1b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397790 - add 'open' active state to urlbar buttons, use a more distinct background colour for it, r=abenson+572682,adw\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7QrhAB79yNw", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-pageActions.js", "browser/base/content/browser-places.js", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_page_action_menu.js", "browser/themes/shared/urlbar-searchbar.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a8d0557f9fc259c35fd047282f06d681461d34a2", "parents": ["ad4a5b8426edef77c9e2ed9aba138083c9937e64"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sam Foster \u003csfoster@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1386726 - Fix alignment of banner item labels in the hamburger menu. r=Gijs\n\n* The start padding should match the 12px defined for nearby toolbarbuttons:\n.subview-subheader, panelview .toolbarbutton-1, .subviewbutton, .widget-overflow-list .toolbarbutton-1\n* Add override for OSX which uses 18px for this padding\n* Adjust margin for the right/end icon in banner items\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 81u97Wf8qXr", "files": ["browser/themes/osx/customizableui/panelUI.css", "browser/themes/shared/customizableui/panelUI.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2bd5e6f268862556ff086477d81d8ed86234be9c", "parents": ["a8d0557f9fc259c35fd047282f06d681461d34a2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Prathiksha \u003cprathikshaprasadsuman@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1400992 - Fix test_safe_browsing_warning_pages.py. r=francois,whimboo\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EIf2ak8Q2YJ", "files": ["testing/firefox-ui/tests/functional/security/test_safe_browsing_warning_pages.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6e57f448953dbd8b5df11682ccc13b022269512d", "parents": ["2bd5e6f268862556ff086477d81d8ed86234be9c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bobby Holley \u003cbobbyholley@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #18566 - Thread state fixes (from bholley:thread_state_fixes); r=Manishearth\n\nhttps://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1400435\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: c6381c66a0bc2b7cad14a808b000d0e38860c7f6", "files": ["servo/components/layout_thread/lib.rs", "servo/components/style/gecko/global_style_data.rs", "servo/components/style/thread_state.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7e1111a6f0521a51e6ca0fe553a40348e5de2ed4", "parents": ["6e57f448953dbd8b5df11682ccc13b022269512d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401170 - Bump startup_timeout to 180s for mochitest and reftests on Buildbot. r=gbrown\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Ixz4hJnW7NN", "files": ["testing/mozharness/configs/unittests/win_unittest.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f659596d56f2074544fa82d019d97074ff0402fc", "parents": ["7e1111a6f0521a51e6ca0fe553a40348e5de2ed4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401170 - Bump startup_timeout to 180s for all reftests. r=gbrown\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HNfmoyLuI1c", "files": ["testing/mozharness/configs/unittests/linux_unittest.py", "testing/mozharness/configs/unittests/mac_unittest.py", "testing/mozharness/configs/unittests/win_taskcluster_unittest.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "60d3233655028c318481f0b546b5875c79cc43a7", "parents": ["f659596d56f2074544fa82d019d97074ff0402fc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 26f9c5c3f434 (bug 1401316) for failing xpcshell's toolkit/modules/tests/xpcshell/test_NewTabUtils.js. r=backout", "files": ["toolkit/modules/NewTabUtils.jsm", "toolkit/modules/tests/xpcshell/test_NewTabUtils.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bb2d70186f6e6c1d9bd6313def70acc1ee8c5487", "parents": ["60d3233655028c318481f0b546b5875c79cc43a7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401118 - Avoid having to modify replace-malloc.mk every time we add an allocator API entry point. r=froydnj\n\nFor obscure linkage reasons, we need all the replace-malloc symbols\nbeing passed to the linker to tell it to allow them being undefined.\n\nThat list actually duplicates what's in malloc_decls.h somehow, and\nevery time we add an entry point, we end up having to modify those two\nfiles (and others, addressed in different bugs), which is suboptimal.\n\nSo we generate the list of those symbols from malloc_decls.h.", "files": ["mozglue/build/replace_malloc.mk"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0ed0593535e0d6fe78550c0e9f5520e79a164a4f", "parents": ["bb2d70186f6e6c1d9bd6313def70acc1ee8c5487"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Wes Kocher \u003cwkocher@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge m-c to autoland, a=merge\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BLgnf5zTCU3", "files": ["dom/webauthn/u2f-hid-rs/build.rs", "dom/webauthn/u2f-hid-rs/src/runloop.rs", "modules/libpref/init/all.js", "taskcluster/docker/android-build/buildprops.json", "taskcluster/docker/android-build/oauth.txt", "taskcluster/docker/recipes/install-mercurial.sh", "taskcluster/scripts/builder/build-android-dependencies/after.sh", "taskcluster/scripts/builder/build-android-dependencies/before.sh", "testing/web-platform/meta/FileAPI/url/url_createobjecturl_blob.html.ini", "toolkit/library/gtest/rust/Cargo.lock", "toolkit/library/rust/Cargo.lock"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "fa4de7ce4de0d9d5fcb4baffa600e439992b9e4b", "parents": ["0ed0593535e0d6fe78550c0e9f5520e79a164a4f", "a0eb21bf55e1c1ae0ba311e6f2273da05c712799"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Felipe Gomes \u003cfelipc@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390706 - Remove Flash CTP rollout addon and make it CTP by default through prefs. r=benjamin+7044\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CPIoiXnx5WT", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/extensions/clicktoplay-rollout/bootstrap.js", "browser/extensions/clicktoplay-rollout/install.rdf.in", "browser/extensions/clicktoplay-rollout/moz.build", "browser/extensions/moz.build", "testing/talos/talos/xtalos/xperf_whitelist.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a6f36a2ff650f7a0cda479bfb5dbf38f199c729d", "parents": ["fa4de7ce4de0d9d5fcb4baffa600e439992b9e4b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xidorn Quan \u003cme@upsuper.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1400540 - Decide style backend type based on principal. r=bholley\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: A4y9Shdbr7g", "files": ["dom/base/nsDocument.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "18723c6944b1d45e0044e100a8fdc8f573df4714", "parents": ["a6f36a2ff650f7a0cda479bfb5dbf38f199c729d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394462 - Update dnsNotFound error copy and illustration. r=nhnt11\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KFp3JhkCDJJ", "files": ["browser/base/content/aboutNetError.xhtml", "browser/base/content/illustrations/error-malformed-url.svg", "browser/base/content/illustrations/error-server-not-found.svg", "browser/base/jar.mn", "browser/locales/en-US/chrome/overrides/appstrings.properties", "browser/locales/en-US/chrome/overrides/netError.dtd", "browser/themes/shared/aboutNetError.css", "devtools/client/inspector/test/browser_inspector_navigate_to_errors.js", "docshell/base/nsDocShell.cpp", "dom/locales/en-US/chrome/appstrings.properties", "mobile/locales/en-US/overrides/appstrings.properties", "toolkit/themes/shared/in-content/info-pages.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "23f0696642c2c375c25119fdb7079b5447ed87c7", "parents": ["18723c6944b1d45e0044e100a8fdc8f573df4714"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nihanth Subramanya \u003cnhnt11@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394458 - Update copy for about:tabcrashed. r=johannh\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Fyx4ug6ZiQO", "files": ["browser/base/content/aboutTabCrashed.xhtml", "browser/locales/en-US/chrome/browser/aboutTabCrashed.dtd"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6a176aa5ce0b0a4fe0b9fbe8f9b76519885ae432", "parents": ["23f0696642c2c375c25119fdb7079b5447ed87c7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nihanth Subramanya \u003cnhnt11@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1398183 - Update copy for about:sessionrestore. r=johannh\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: ET2zEKsS7SM", "files": ["browser/components/sessionstore/content/aboutSessionRestore.xhtml", "browser/locales/en-US/chrome/browser/aboutSessionRestore.dtd"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "332b5c019493e543ee322d9a0b84312e573035b9", "parents": ["6a176aa5ce0b0a4fe0b9fbe8f9b76519885ae432"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Blake Kaplan \u003cmrbkap@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1398396 - Make locale functions take a runtime instead of a context. r=janv,jorendorff\n\nMost of these functions already solely operate on the runtime even though they\ntake a context. That leads to confusion at the API user level since it looks\nlike they're stored on the context. JS_GetDefaultLocale still takes a context\nbecause it actually does use the passed-in context.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4d0LQIBExvg", "files": ["js/src/jsapi-tests/testDateToLocaleString.cpp", "js/src/jsapi-tests/testIntlAvailableLocales.cpp", "js/src/jsapi.cpp", "js/src/jsapi.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9980c7c2f2314036dcf4b95b8f7ea8070dd9d9cf", "parents": ["332b5c019493e543ee322d9a0b84312e573035b9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Blake Kaplan \u003cmrbkap@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1398396 - Initialize the locale stuff on runtimes instead of contexts. r=billm\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Il9HAqYdTzK", "files": ["dom/workers/RuntimeService.cpp", "js/xpconnect/src/XPCJSContext.cpp", "js/xpconnect/src/XPCJSRuntime.cpp", "js/xpconnect/src/XPCLocale.cpp", "js/xpconnect/src/xpcprivate.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ffddadd962f2abdefb81b2252cc49911b33a8e89", "parents": ["9980c7c2f2314036dcf4b95b8f7ea8070dd9d9cf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401288 - Run remote devtools panel browsers in the right TabGroup. r=aswan\n\nThis patch ensures that the devtools panel browser elements are associated to\nthe same TabGroup of the other extension pages from the same extension.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 40TSPqGfTnz", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/ext-devtools-panels.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3e84d38ad0b4c7dd46b73663094895fe76f088fe", "parents": ["ffddadd962f2abdefb81b2252cc49911b33a8e89"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401101 - Remove the generic replace-malloc library. r=njn\n\nIt is one of the moving parts when adding new memory allocation APIs.\n\nIt was added in bug 1168719 and the only thing that actually used it\nwas the sampling-based memory profiler, which was removed in bug\n1385953. We however keep the replace-malloc bridge entry point so that\nsomething else, in the future, may still provide the feature.", "files": ["memory/replace/moz.build", "memory/replace/replace/ReplaceMalloc.cpp", "memory/replace/replace/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f8408a832d3514aa8d88d43ce26b138a52919a04", "parents": ["3e84d38ad0b4c7dd46b73663094895fe76f088fe"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401116 - Remove jemalloc symbols from mozglue.def.in. r=njn\n\nAs long as symbols have the right declspec, the linker is going to\nexport them as expected. The main exception to when we actually need the\nexported symbol to have a different name, which is the case for the\nsymbols normally exported by the CRT. So keep only those renamed symbols\nin mozglue.def.in.\n\nKeeping the jemalloc symbols in this file kind of implies that we need\nevery new API entry points to appear in there when it's not true. This\nthus removes an unnecessary moving part when adding new allocator API\nentry points.", "files": ["mozglue/build/mozglue.def.in"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "af468f61fe8a0ee33de3f4558e46217c1ee6d172", "parents": ["f8408a832d3514aa8d88d43ce26b138a52919a04"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thom Chiovoloni \u003ctchiovoloni@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393659 - Fix inconsistent handling of max_post_bytes and max_request_bytes r=markh\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4jwpAYNuoQj", "files": ["services/sync/modules/constants.js", "services/sync/modules/engines.js", "services/sync/modules/engines/tabs.js", "services/sync/modules/record.js", "services/sync/modules/service.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_postqueue.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_syncengine_sync.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_tab_engine.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_tab_store.js", "tools/lint/eslint/modules.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4c95e94b973b1b57965f23f3126119ce7d37671b", "parents": ["af468f61fe8a0ee33de3f4558e46217c1ee6d172"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Comella \u003cmichael.l.comella@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401385: Add Pin to Top Sites to missing configurations. r=liuche\n\nWhen I implemented this, I forgot to add it to non-phone configurations.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4zTrYZm5tXR", "files": ["mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-large-v26/browser_app_menu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-large/browser_app_menu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-v26/browser_app_menu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-xlarge-v26/browser_app_menu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-xlarge/browser_app_menu.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9d24dfb51c504a3543b69007eae9924fffb9dd0f", "parents": ["4c95e94b973b1b57965f23f3126119ce7d37671b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mantaroh Yoshinaga \u003cmantaroh@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1362817 - Use PRTime instead of time_t in nsSimplePageSequenceFrame::Reflow. r=m_kato\n\nThe nsSimplePageSequenceFrame::Reflow calls DateTimeFormat::FormatTime().\nIn 32 bit environment, this conversion will overflow. So this patch will use\nDateTimeFormat::FormatPRTime() instead of it.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3b1GhlrJDKM", "files": ["layout/generic/nsSimplePageSequenceFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "16deccf18876816db354f58165e1eef7500e2357", "parents": ["9d24dfb51c504a3543b69007eae9924fffb9dd0f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mantaroh Yoshinaga \u003cmantaroh@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1362817 - Drop the DateTimeFormat::FormatTime(). r=m_kato\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JuNaLYhWCHI", "files": ["intl/locale/DateTimeFormat.cpp", "intl/locale/DateTimeFormat.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ddad6d9b200eeced73e7286c9be93bbd877c7db5", "parents": ["16deccf18876816db354f58165e1eef7500e2357"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicholas Nethercote \u003cnnethercote@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #18568 - Measure the UA cache (from nnethercote:bug-1400078); r=emilio\n\nThis is the Servo PR for https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1400078\n\n\u003c!-- Please describe your changes on the following line: --\u003e\n\n---\n\u003c!-- Thank you for contributing to Servo! Please replace each `[ ]` by `[X]` when the step is complete, and replace `__` with appropriate data: --\u003e\n- [X] `./mach build -d` does not report any errors\n- [X] `./mach test-tidy` does not report any errors\n- [X] These changes fix https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1400078\n\n\u003c!-- Either: --\u003e\n- [ ] There are tests for these changes OR\n- [X] These changes do not require tests because tested on Gecko side.\n\n\u003c!-- Also, please make sure that \"Allow edits from maintainers\" checkbox is checked, so that we can help you if you get stuck somewhere along the way.--\u003e\n\n\u003c!-- Pull requests that do not address these steps are welcome, but they will require additional verification as part of the review process. --\u003e\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: ad4f50270d12564da471489c703119fc4a57fa15", "files": ["servo/components/style/applicable_declarations.rs", "servo/components/style/gecko/generated/bindings.rs", "servo/components/style/gecko/generated/structs_debug.rs", "servo/components/style/gecko/generated/structs_release.rs", "servo/components/style/selector_parser.rs", "servo/components/style/stylist.rs", "servo/ports/geckolib/glue.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8d9db6f7a86ed2a829b086a4cc15d5ad32af8279", "parents": ["ddad6d9b200eeced73e7286c9be93bbd877c7db5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicholas Nethercote \u003cnnethercote@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1400078 - Measure the UA cache. r=njn.\n\nServoStyleSetSizes now has two uses, one for the Stylist, and one for the UA\ncache, and so the patch removes 'Stylist' from the field names.\n\nExample output from about:memory:\n\n\u003e +----1,359,608 B (00.55%) -- layout\n\u003e |    +----756,488 B (00.31%) -- style-sheet-cache [2]\n\u003e |    +----393,968 B (00.16%) -- servo-ua-cache\n\u003e |    |    +--234,496 B (00.10%) -- element-and-pseudos-maps\n\u003e |    |    +---59,648 B (00.02%) -- revalidation-selectors\n\u003e |    |    +---58,320 B (00.02%) -- invalidation-map\n\u003e |    |    +---30,752 B (00.01%) -- other\n\u003e |    |    +---10,752 B (00.00%) -- precomputed-pseudos\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8oxuJO0ojp", "files": ["dom/base/nsWindowMemoryReporter.cpp", "dom/base/nsWindowSizes.h", "layout/style/ServoBindingList.h", "layout/style/ServoBindings.cpp", "layout/style/ServoStyleSet.cpp", "layout/style/ServoStyleSet.h", "layout/style/ServoTypes.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2b9dcbd0701a739568267ba2a2614ac0be9ae3b9", "parents": ["8d9db6f7a86ed2a829b086a4cc15d5ad32af8279"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicholas Nethercote \u003cnnethercote@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401427 - Temporarily disable UACacheReporter due to a leak.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: G8MBeSqYkqa", "files": ["layout/style/ServoBindings.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6b2618acffea72ab7e06116680365ad352660823", "parents": ["2b9dcbd0701a739568267ba2a2614ac0be9ae3b9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Louis Chang \u003clochang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1290782 Part 1 - When drawing a border-image using an SVG image, we should not take into account any transformation of currentMatrix when computing svg viewport size. r=cjku,dholbert\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8rkwQGKJOvo", "files": ["layout/base/nsLayoutUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4dade7ac1e2403d693d59b8501a04c3e043d38ec", "parents": ["6b2618acffea72ab7e06116680365ad352660823"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Louis Chang \u003clochang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1290782 Part 2 - Remove redundant destCtx and IsEmpty check of snappedDestSize since it should always have a value. r=cjku\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 25IlXeqURVa", "files": ["layout/base/nsLayoutUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f00ccd10b4f55dd290b4d12e8819c4718c41f7de", "parents": ["4dade7ac1e2403d693d59b8501a04c3e043d38ec"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Louis Chang \u003clochang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1290782 Part 3 - Add test cases for using an SVG image as border-image. r=cjku,dholbert\n\nMozReview-