null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7785": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Layzell \u003cmichael@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401685 - Don't skip sending BHR ping if it is empty, r=froydnj\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/backgroundhangmonitor/BHRTelemetryService.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "06eacffae8c8d2bec170b2ad6e6bfa4f95410e39", "parents": ["789e21a08030b00acd832a58268680dede2e7a1b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nathan Froyd \u003cfroydnj@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401662 - don't inline nsThreadManager::get(); r=erahm\n\nDefining get() in the declaration of nsThreadManager implicitly sticks\nan \"inline\" on the function, which is not what we want: inlining it\nspreads around a lot of static initialization code.  Providing an\nout-of-line definition is much better in terms of code size.", "files": ["xpcom/threads/nsThreadManager.cpp", "xpcom/threads/nsThreadManager.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a88ee0137c104a57c747cd129c45952ccf1431ad", "parents": ["06eacffae8c8d2bec170b2ad6e6bfa4f95410e39"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1373843 - Add -fsanitize-coverage to cflags in nicer.gyp; r=posidron\n\nI missed doing this in the original patch because my mozconfig defined the\nCFLAGS globally to include -fsanitize-coverage.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4QdiIgdfAm2", "files": ["media/mtransport/third_party/nICEr/nicer.gyp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node"