ntainer name. r=jaws, a=sledru", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/containers.xul", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/containers.xul", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser.ini", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser_containers_name_input.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "95731178131ba56c927d83f5f36caf6592662d87", "parents": ["961888633c2ca07ed7cdfa70d7740c8fd7b9deba"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Oriol Brufau \u003coriol-bugzilla@hotmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1399265 - Avoid relayout when switching tab in devtools. r=Honza, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: J0vsN0MiN1o", "files": ["devtools/client/shared/components/tabs/tabs.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "45b0a92887e4bc705de7081430b0b1d9a432df24", "parents": ["95731178131ba56c927d83f5f36caf6592662d87"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402066 - Part 1: Fix ordering of base schema data in extension child processes. r=aswan, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FtLHJq5H5oD", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/Schemas.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/extension-process-script.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c4554c786af525028a97417650e8e6949e34ee68", "parents": ["45b0a92887e4bc705de7081430b0b1d9a432df24"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402066 - Part 2: Enable permissions tests in OOP mode. r=aswan, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4Tv2HAaSV19", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionXPCShellUtils.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_permissions.js", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_redirects.js", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell-common.ini", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e73836222b5775c7f81a46da0aef49db642e644f", "parents": ["c4554c786af525028a97417650e8e6949e34ee68"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402592 - Ensure that ImageBridgeParent instances are closed by the parent during shutdown. r=dvander, a=sledru\n\nWe currently allow the content process to shutdown the IPDL objects on\nbehalf the parent, and we wait for all of these instances to be freed\nbefore we complete shutdown. This is undesirable because it requires the\nparent to trust the child rather than the other way around; the child\ncan hold shutdown hostage by simply not releasing its instances. The\nchild should already support the parent closing its graphics IPDL\nobjects because the GPU process itself can die abruptly and be restored\nat a later time.", "files": ["gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorThread.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/ImageBridgeChild.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/ImageBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/ImageBridgeParent.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "94e44c1f0875288e2612bcdff3f93f2b663b7909", "parents": ["e73836222b5775c7f81a46da0aef49db642e644f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kearwood \"Kip\" Gilbert \u003ckgilbert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1381085 - Submit VR frames with a separate ID3DDeviceContextState. r=dmu, a=sledru\n\n- Using a separate ID3DDeviceContextState ensures\n  that the WebVR context does not stomp over the\n  mirrored state used by the MLGPU \"Advanced\" Layers rendering.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 99mfdsjFrMI", "files": ["dom/vr/test/reftest/reftest.list", "gfx/vr/VRDisplayHost.cpp", "gfx/vr/VRDisplayHost.h", "gfx/vr/gfxVROculus.cpp", "gfx/vr/gfxVROculus.h", "gfx/vr/gfxVRPuppet.cpp", "gfx/vr/gfxVRPuppet.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c7091b22d32efde7e224cb7b7671c121905a52bf", "parents": ["94e44c1f0875288e2612bcdff3f93f2b663b7909"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jing-wei Wu \u003ctopwu.tw@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401871 - Check if menu item(home_add_to_launcher) exists or not before accessing it. r=nechen, a=sledru\n\nWe temporarily hide `home_add_to_launcher` in API 26, which means directly accesses it without checking\nif it exists or not would cause NullPointerException.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KXnP81ZZa6u", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/home/HomeFragment.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "06cffe71eae8e440915e5b62c80629ed5c539ba7", "parents": ["c7091b22d32efde7e224cb7b7671c121905a52bf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402876 - Remove unnecessary InvalidateCompilerOutputsForScript call. r=nbp, a=sledru", "files": ["js/src/jit/Ion.cpp", "js/src/vm/TypeInference.cpp", "js/src/vm/TypeInference.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f06912ba5bb7ac2951eb184ba8d2f9f2487f1e4d", "parents": ["06cffe71eae8e440915e5b62c80629ed5c539ba7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1403251 - Only display validation message when element is invalid. r=sebastian, a=sledru\n\nOnly display form validation message when the element becomes invalid\nafter an invalid submission, by checking the \"-moz-ui-invalid\"\npseudo-class.\n\nAlso fix some message visibility bugs, by making sure in more places\nthat we only display messages for focused elements.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 16rvMmu8Zj6", "files": ["mobile/android/modules/FormAssistant.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f2db1ec2bf72db9f4d164188e6173a90412939d1", "parents": ["f06912ba5bb7ac2951eb184ba8d2f9f2487f1e4d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Henning \u003cjh+bugzilla@buttercookie.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1403693 - Fix IDN conversion during theme installation. r=jwu, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9WshGSu4FQJ", "files": ["mobile/android/chrome/content/browser.js"], "git_node"