d regexps when extensions.formautofill.creditCards.available is false. r=lchang, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2WPBtJrKGJL", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillHeuristics.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/unit/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dd4bcf227b95d5a8767b3873f85b16c4c7eafd09", "parents": ["c048148b2f2d6ea31c20d9068947bbb7945348bf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Woodrow \u003cmwoodrow@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397671 - Don't treat SVG transformed frames as being transformed for the purposes of computing Combines3DTransformWithAncestors. r=dbaron, a=sledru", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFrame.cpp", "layout/generic/nsIFrame.h", "layout/reftests/transform-3d/preserve3d-8-ref.html", "layout/reftests/transform-3d/preserve3d-8.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "54a5c274f8a49ce12cf560e3d715ab9e922dec52", "parents": ["dd4bcf227b95d5a8767b3873f85b16c4c7eafd09"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Mathies \u003cjmathies@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401561 - Avoid prompting about compatibility issues with JAWS when e10s is pref'd off. r=jaws, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2ejZ7Ga2lLk", "files": ["browser/components/nsBrowserGlue.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "75e965089708d0937fad036eff7e3fce01994e0e", "parents": ["54a5c274f8a49ce12cf560e3d715ab9e922dec52"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390025 - Add separator between the tab strip and the drag space in front of it. r=johannh, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LOymOHgg8fr", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.css", "browser/base/content/browser.xul", "browser/themes/shared/browser.inc.css", "browser/themes/shared/tabs.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8a3071abbaf1a1f5e8ad810480abc5f265e3cb12", "parents": ["75e965089708d0937fad036eff7e3fce01994e0e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402469 - Part 1. Return value of ConvertListType should use Element instead of nsresult. r=masayuki, a=sledru\n\nThis is a typo bug of Bug 1053779 Part 2.  ConvertListType might return NS_OK\neven if ReplaceContainer doesn't return valid value.\n\nSo, to clean up code, we should return Element instead of nsresult since out\nparameter of this function is Element only.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 44UHETzcdGy", "files": ["editor/libeditor/HTMLEditRules.cpp", "editor/libeditor/HTMLEditRules.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1a9b1dc1e690c62655a86996411947f1aa2d772b", "parents": ["8a3071abbaf1a1f5e8ad810480abc5f265e3cb12"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402469 - Part 2. Add crash test. r=masayuki, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HogVH2OTyd6", "files": ["editor/libeditor/crashtests/1402469.html", "editor/libeditor/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "afebd547493aa4a6799603fca0f23ca2e9056f60", "parents": ["1a9b1dc1e690c62655a86996411947f1aa2d772b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402681 - Part 1: Do not queue the task without task queue. r=jya, a=sledru\n\nSince the source buffer is a wrapped native, it would be unlinked twice and then the\nTrackBuffersManager::Detach() would also be called twice.\n\nThe first detach task would clear the task queue of TrackBuffersManager, and then we\nwon't accept any new task without task queue. The second detach task should not be\nexecuted.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: AWTzVbRH5B1", "files": ["dom/media/mediasource/TrackBuffersManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "23eb5e8f91148dab8b9752e3d663a3b5aedaa7cb", "parents": ["afebd547493aa4a6799603fca0f23ca2e9056f60"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402681 - Part 2: Add log. r=jya, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8qINxSCKrvg", "files": ["dom/media/mediasource/SourceBufferTask.h", "dom/media/mediasource/TrackBuffersManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b108bdcaff9d3ec05cd3eba32800b3393409126c", "parents": ["23eb5e8f91148dab8b9752e3d663a3b5aedaa7cb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1389759 - Ensure we tear down CompositorManagerChild correctly if init or the GPU process fail. r=dvander, a=sledru", "files": ["gfx/ipc/GPUProcessManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorManagerChild.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorManagerChild.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorManagerParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorManagerParent.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b7b894f5fad8b4fb79e60b6bbdcce52da1281714", "parents": ["b108bdcaff9d3ec05cd3eba32800b3393409126c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1506952072, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7871": {"changesets": [{"author": "cku \u003ccku@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402798 - Part 1. Check the type of an SVGPaint object from the correct frame. r=longsonr, a=sledru\n\nmTargetFrame is not a correct one, we should check the SVGStyle of 'frame'\nobject.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3UNfbXkICkz", "files": ["layout/svg/SVGObserverUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "eef9559e379b51c1c5ac6a22a1e29ee2c2111f8d", "parents": ["b7b894f5fad8b4fb79e60b6bbdcce52da1281714"], "tags": []}, {"author": "cku \u003ccku@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402798 - Part 2. Add a crash test for applying fill:url() property to an SVG text element. r=longsonr, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LqkK3Z5sYTB", "files": ["dom/svg/crashtests/1402798.html", "dom/svg/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1ce3b4548c147f7403e9ddab1591229f1bc6803a", "parents": ["eef9559e379b51c1c5ac6a22a1e29ee2c2111f8d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Haik Aftandilian \u003chaftandilian@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402205 - Non-existent background page blocks extension startup. r=kmag, a=sledru\n\nAdd calls to OnStartRequest() and OnStopRequest() to properly handle async\nread failures for remote JAR's and remote unpacked extension resources.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Dcg0LDht9B9", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/res/ExtensionProtocolHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "667e147f2e0ab7edb6843a3b4cc9f1f8d1756e9b", "parents": ["1ce3b4548c147f7403e9ddab1591229f1bc6803a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ray Lin \u003cralin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397486 - Update controlBar width according to videocontrols which really grows along \u003caudio\u003e width. r=jaws, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LpxH7Pnu7tQ", "files": ["toolkit/content/tests/widgets/head.js", "toolkit/content/tests/widgets/test_audiocontrols_dimensions.html", "toolkit/content/widgets/videocontrols.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6966674d52788c45016b8d9c2cb958503d349e52", "parents": ["667e147f2e0ab7edb6843a3b4cc9f1f8d1756e9b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dale Harvey \u003cdale@arandomurl.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1399642 - Use photon search icon in awesomebar. r=dao, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Dzf8DqrGRam", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_identity_indication.js", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/data/content/activity-stream.css", "browser/themes/linux/browser.css", "browser/themes/osx/browser.css", "browser/themes/shared/customizableui/panelUI.inc.css", "browser/themes/shared/icons/find.svg", "browser/themes/shared/icons/search-glass.svg", "browser/themes/shared/identity-block/identity-block.inc.css", "browser/themes/shared/jar.inc.mn"