branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401522 - Don't apply statusCode sent from parent if mCanceled or mStatus has been modified in the child. r=mayhemer, a=ritu\n\nWhen a WyciwygChannel is canceled, but WyciwygChannelParent::RecvCancel happens\nafter WyciwygChannelParent::SendOnStartRequest, it would send statusCode=NS_OK\nto WyciwygChannelChild::OnStartRequest. So we should not apply the statusCode\nif mCanceled, just like how HttpChannelChild handles it.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5H3PUrlArIA", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/wyciwyg/WyciwygChannelChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "47c55e4e8ec9865cef8c89dde84cae15ebf8d062", "parents": ["c016aa44063766846c261a5eb998b364cb10e229"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1404651 - Keep focus in the tabstrip when the focus has shifted with the arrow keys. r=dao, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Brm9jImW9bc", "files": ["browser/base/content/tabbrowser.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "261ad1333984d97f050d74157f52523098f7ff14", "parents": ["47c55e4e8ec9865cef8c89dde84cae15ebf8d062"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike de Boer \u003cmdeboer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1405942 - Make sure to always apply the descriptionHeightWorkaround in Photon panels on popupshown, because it might've missed elements that were hidden. r=Paolo, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9xSqoZGJ3MF", "files": ["browser/components/customizableui/PanelMultiView.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "567e84287828cffa7f68dd45bcef816ee9525da5", "parents": ["261ad1333984d97f050d74157f52523098f7ff14"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ian Bicking \u003cianb@colorstudy.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1407732 - Update Screenshots version to 19.2.0. r=_6a68, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HR7EF6z7g2F", "files": ["browser/extensions/screenshots/install.rdf", "browser/extensions/screenshots/webextension/m