u003e 6e3dfa0ea030\nru -\u003e 760cda086381\nzh-CN -\u003e 8aff87add86f", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "589e3a5d08ab72299b90b8ec30a334ad19097434", "parents": ["b3ed60185d530b41be0a0ce54cbbccb416a40c4d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1509542413, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8107": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nbg -\u003e f5cbdea3b4bb\nff -\u003e 0ae0e4ad0400", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d705fd06d8e5440b202b9e6bbc440488b503bc8f", "parents": ["589e3a5d08ab72299b90b8ec30a334ad19097434"], "tags": []}], "date": 1509546062, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8108": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging aa8f74f0ad60ab35955e539ac8e1164fe00a7fd1 with FENNEC_57_0b13_BUILD1, FENNEC_57_0b13_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ef4109cb756c28e7548d664026928e8a6ec38abc", "parents": ["d705fd06d8e5440b202b9e6bbc440488b503bc8f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1509567940, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8109": {"changesets": [{"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1412222 - start_session should not ignore the result of connection attempts. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nBy silently ignoring the result from 'wait_for_port' results in a\ndelayed socket error, which sometimes can cause strange results\nas seen on bug 1410366.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2ptIwX6upBG", "files": ["testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/marionette.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bd0f72296cf1ead39e07489c1ead33074cbadd78", "parents": ["ef4109cb756c28e7548d664026928e8a6ec38abc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1405474 - Add more attributes for elements in pprint output. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nCurrently pprint only checks for 'id' and 'class', and adds\nthose to the output. Given that lots of elements might not\nhave those attributes a couple more should be added, which\ncan help to uniquly identify those.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3thefe4oLN3", "files": ["testing/marionette/error.js", "testing/marionette/test_error.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "79dba93cef4e19e50ef6bde2fb0e6e4137f2d754", "parents": ["bd0f72296cf1ead39e07489c1ead33074cbadd78"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Blake Kaplan \u003cmrbkap@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1403428 - Handle a rare error case more gracefully. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nIn certain rare cases, it's possible for a previous test to close a window\nbetween the executor getting the window list and trying to close the needed\nwindows.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GTzoOxBaPwl", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/wptrunner/executors/executormarionette.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3972e3b8eedfa27a95116279bff8392c085ec144", "parents": ["79dba93cef4e19e50ef6bde2fb0e6e4137f2d754"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1403180 - Fix StripHandlerFromOBJREF for VT_DISPATCH on Windows 7. r=aklotz, a=ritu\n\nStripHandlerFromOBJREF shortens the OBJREF by sizeof(CLSID), so it needs to seek the stream back after tweaking the OBJREF.\nPreviously, this was done using a relative seek.\nUnfortunately, for some reason I can't fathom on Windows 7, this doesn't work when marshaling for VT_DISPATCH.\nThe Seek call succeeds, but either does nothing or sets the stream position to a garbage value.\nInstead, we now use an absolute seek, which seems to behave.\nThis was breaking IAccessible::accNavigate and AccessibleChildren on Windows 7.\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FEH93oiyP5R", "files": ["ipc/mscom/Objref.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c81df7f7b71fb5056b32eba3d9eff4136bc5719a", "parents": ["3972e3b8eedfa27a95116279bff8392c085ec144"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Henning \u003cjh+bugzilla@buttercookie.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1405973 - Add white to basic colour picker. r=jwu, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4Cfxrj8SYGQ", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/widget/BasicColorPicker.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7591c7732048a08c2adb1337461da7f41dcc4274", "parents": ["c81df7f7b71fb5056b32eba3d9eff4136bc5719a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Chronopoulos \u003cachronop@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1411866 - Uplift cubeb import to cf5ddc5. r=padenot, a=ritu", "files": ["media/libcubeb/bug-1411866-beta-uplift.patch", "media/libcubeb/src/cubeb_audiounit.cpp", "media/libcubeb/src/cubeb_utils.h", "media/libcubeb/update.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b1dc78a5838b3bef69b4ae4d2c0c9bc351ef9ff7", "parents": ["7591c7732048a08c2adb1337461da7f41dcc4274"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Fred Lin \u003cgasolin@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1408539 - Onboarding Tour: update customize, library, and screenshot illustration. r=Fischer, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KHab4CFeLdQ", "files": ["browser/extensions/onboarding/content/img/figure_customize.svg", "browser/extensions/onboarding/content/img/figure_library.svg", "browser/extensions/onboarding/content/img/figure_screenshots.svg"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3e4524e4b17905dcc3a854b581bac2391af46119", "parents": ["b1dc78a5838b3bef69b4ae4d2c0c9bc351ef9ff7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Varga \u003cjan.varga@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1410420 - Clear database actor's strong reference to IDBDatabase when opening of a database fails. r=asuth, a=ritu", "files": ["dom/indexedDB/ActorsChild.cpp", "dom/indexedDB/ActorsChild.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3c66b352d3fb105bdde6b731c16a41348cfc85a4", "parents": ["3e4524e4b17905dcc3a854b581bac2391af46119"], "tags": []}], "date": 1509578656, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "8110": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changesets e35c13737463 and 337db7b083a7 (bug 1406032) for causing various regressions.", "files": ["toolkit/content/tests/chrome/window_largemenu.xul", "widget/cocoa/nsCocoaWindow.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0363254a02688c91f47944e79ea4530d8c29c10f", "parents": ["3c66b352d3fb105bdde6b731c16a41348cfc85a4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1403348 - Add debugging assertions for more AsyncStartup failure modes. r=baku, a=ritu\n\nSince we don't currently know where or how loading the service is failing, we\nneed logging in two places:\n\n1) In ServiceWorkerRegistrar, which will tell us about any JS errors that\noccur in the factory constructor.\n\n2) In the XPConnect module loader, which will tell us about any JS errors\nwhich happen while loading the top-level module script.\n\nIf the load fails due to a non-JS error, we'll simply get a nsresult failure\ncode, which well be less informative, but will still tell us something about\nthe failure mode.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1CsDegJfiho", "files": ["dom/workers/ServiceWorkerRegistrar.cpp", "js/xpconnect/loader/mozJSComponentLoader.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "37480b2c19eb3f29969c2c82191fb527fb9cdcba", "parents": ["0363254a02688c91f47944e79ea4530d8c29c10f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1404743 - Add better diagnostic crash reasons for URLPreloader failure. r=mccr8, data-r=rweiss, a=ritu\n\nThe crash reports for this section of code suggest that in some cases, we're\nending up with a null Omnijar archive when trying to pre-load files. Since the\npre-load file list is determined in the previous session, and the startup\ncache (where the pre-load list is stored) is cleared whenever the build ID\nchanges, it should never be possible for the given omnijar archive to be\nmissing here.\n\nThese crashes also tend to appear in conjunction with crashes due to failures\nin the GetSharedGlobal function, and may have a similar cause.\n\nThis change adds better diagnostic information to these crashes, and should at\nleast tell us which omnijar archive we're failing to get, and the archive path\nthat caused us to load that archive. It may not tell us much, but it may point\nto data corruption, or provide some other clues.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EKq3r4eG5ii", "files": ["js/xpconnect/loader/URLPreloader.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5ce3ede2222347365d2527d93f583f34a30649e2", "parents": ["37480b2c19eb3f29969c2c82191fb527fb9cdcba"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jared Wein \u003cjwein@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413247 - Remove whimsycorn references from #PanelUI since it is unreachable in Firefox57. r=mconley, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: f5xpP6fdWY", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/customizableui/panelUI.inc.css", "browser/themes/shared/customizableui/whimsy.png", "browser/themes/shared/customizableui/whimsy@2x.png", "browser/themes/shared/jar.inc.mn"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "339cb803bbedd811d26e3748ef0b9f2b670b851d", "parents": ["5ce3ede2222347365d2527d93f583f34a30649e2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Randell Jesup \u003crjesup@jesup.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1400563 - More DataChannelConnection shutdown cleanup. r=drno, a=ritu", "files": ["netwerk/sctp/datachannel/DataChannel.cpp", "netwerk/sctp/datachannel/DataChannel.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b729ddecf1d1807b64705588702d2d70b6cc87d8", "parents": ["339cb803bbedd811d26e3748ef0b9f2b670b851d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Randell Jesup \u003crjesup@jesup.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1400563 - Fix leaked nsTArray. r=froydnj, a=ritu", "files": ["netwerk/sctp/datachannel/DataChannel.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ba08d4e02e0c3839aa85985c7fcdf68bba94dac5", "parents": ["b729ddecf1d1807b64705588702d2d70b6cc87d8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1406358 - Keep SpeechDelegate object until speaking is finished. r=eeejay, a=ritu\n\nThe delegate property of NSSpeechSynthesizer doesn't seem to add refcount from 10.13, so we have to keep SpeechDelegate object until speech is finished.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EVtMOPytkjR", "files": ["dom/media/webspeech/synth/cocoa/OSXSpeechSynthesizerService.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "24b1d36cd71070d9a8b7b6b719139351d62f5167", "parents": ["ba08d4e02e0c3839aa85985c7fcdf68bba94dac5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eden Chuang \u003cechuang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1408734 - Return InvalidStateError when accessing ServiceWorkerRegistration::updateViaCache after unregister. r=bkelly, a=ritu\n\nThis patch implements followings\n1. Adding extended attribute [Throws] on ServiceWorkerRegistration\n   ::updateViaCacheattribute.\n2. Instead of calling MOZ_ASSERT, returning InvalidStateError when fail to\n   get the registration in ServiceWorkerRegistration::GetUpdateViaCache().\n3. Adding a new mochitest test_bug1408734.html to reproduce the bug\n   introduced by accessing ServiceWorkerRegistration::updateViaCache after\n   unregister() finishes.", "files": ["dom/webidl/ServiceWorkerRegistration.webidl", "dom/workers/ServiceWorkerRegistration.cpp", "dom/workers/ServiceWorkerRegistration.h", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/mochitest.ini", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/test_bug1408734.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "39275addee5933725bdaf7f5de328e47df39790a", "parents": ["24b1d36cd71070d9a8b7b6b719139351d62f5167"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Marco Castelluccio \u003cmcastelluccio@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1385542 - Blocklist pghook.dll as it causes crashes. r=jimm, a=ritu", "files": ["mozglue/build/WindowsDllBlocklist.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "84af2700ac30dfc0e80759c17f66b46b9733021b", "parents": ["39275addee5933725bdaf7f5de328e47df39790a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Aaron Klotz \u003caklotz@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1336971 - Ensure that we always re-examine the length of the top-level remote doc array to pick up any changes due to mutation. r=Jamie, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BLq1zzyKs9e", "files": ["accessible/windows/msaa/AccessibleWrap.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "05e050d6c86867f19590b72a6131713df81044aa", "parents": ["84af2700ac30dfc0e80759c17f66b46b9733021b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yura Zenevich \u003cyura.zenevich@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1412358 - Add telemetry probes for actions on accessibility indicator button and accessibility privacy preference checkbox. r=jimm, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4xXbf5UwnWK", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/privacy.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Scalars.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d57f1c698b4e2930c64d4beeceb294b0184aae31", "parents": ["05e050d6c86867f19590b72a6131713df81044aa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1412126 - ACTION_EXTERNAL_APPLICATIONS_AVAILABLE no longer needed for Stumbler. r=snorp, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8qGk7nok7Hy", "files": ["mobile/android/stumbler/manifests/StumblerManifest_services.xml.in"